    "body": "YES!!!!!!!!\n\nSo I ran cmd.exe as Administrator, glorious stuck-at-80 column widths and all. Went into the app directory and ran `node_modules\\atom-package-manager\\bin\\apm install .` And it worked! Got the build folder, can `--exec \"require('node-hid')\"` and most importantly, the app runs now too finally!!1!\n\nWhy does `apm` need admin permissions? Or is this actually more to do with running it under \"Git Bash\" rather than cmd.exe?\n"
